ctions. Its social order was one of subjection and subversion, as officials struggled for order and inmates struggled for autonomy.Toth's formidable archival work exposes the nature of the relationships between, and among, prisoners and administrators. He explores the daily grind of existence: living conditions, discipline, labor, sex, and violence. Thus, he gives voice to the incarcerated, not simply to the incarcerators, whose ideas and agendas tend to dominate the historical record. Mettray is, above all else, a deeply personal illumination of life inside France's most venerated carceral institution.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aJuvenile correctionszFrancexHistory. 0aJuvenile delinquentsxRehabilitationzFrance. 0aJuvenile detention homeszFrancexHistory. 0aProblem childrenxInstitutional carezFrancexHistory. 0aReformatorieszFrancexHistory. 4aCriminology. 4aHistory. 4aWest European History. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh  aagricultural colonies, prisoners, social control, 19th century, 20th century, France.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065198008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501740190?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501740190423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501740190/original  a978-3-11-061017-8  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-